ken-for-granted aspects of what it means to age in an ageist society. Part of the Ageing in a Global Context series, the two parts address the materialities and the embodiments of everyday life respectively. Topics covered include household possessions, public and private spaces, older drivers, media representations, dementia care, health-tracking, dress and sexuality. This focus on micro-sociological conditions allows us to rethink key questions which have shaped debates in the social aspects of ageing. International contributions, including from the UK, USA, Sweden and Canada, provide a critical guide to inform thinking and planning our ageing futures.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 70(DE-601)1045167200(DE-588)4068596-2aAltern2gnd 70(DE-601)1063975910(DE-588)4001307-8aAlltag2gnd 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Gerontology.2bisacsh1 aAndrews, Gavin J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBraedley, Susan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCalasanti, Toni, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChivers, Sally, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aClarke, Laura Hurd, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEkerdt, David J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGish, Jessica A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGrenier, Amanda M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGrigorovich, Alisa, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKatz, Stephen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKatz, Stephen, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aKontos, Pia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/rela